race.description: Queens Wharf Tower 5, Brisbane Qtis 3YO Mdn Hcp
race.comment: LA PROFECIA (3) debuts for the premier stable and has looked sharp at the Deagon trials. Has an awkward gate but has a handy 2kg claim and can win if the betting suggests stable confidence. Of the raced, ENFORCEABLE (1) sets the standard. Brought strong form to resumption and led missing a whisker from a wide gate. Draws out again, but he's fast and will be fitter. He has plenty up the sleeve. NARUKAMI (4) debuts and should be advantaged by the inside barrier. Won his latest trial at the Sunshine Coast, and a bold run is likely. I AM PIETRA (8) brings a close up placing from Toowoomba and can build on that. LA BIANCA (11) ran a promising enough race on debut for the Freedman yard, and quick improvement is likely.
